This paper deals with a type theory for defining logics and proofs, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses dependent types, which are commonly used in programming languages and verification systems, leading to cs.PL (Programming Languages) as another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions metaprogramming and reflection, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE) and computational logic (cs.CL), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses a model for proving normalization, which is a topic related to proof theory (cs.LF).
